We know that $v(x) = 33futhi$ where $futhi$ is some integer. Therefore, all multiples of $v(x)$ are of the form $33kfuthi$ for some integer $k$. Now, let's check whether $u(x)$ divides each of these multiples:

$$\begin{aligned}
u(x) \divides (33kfuthi) \Rightarrow u(x) &= 0 \\
\Rightarrow k &= 0 \text{ or } k &= 11 \text{ modulo 33}
\end{aligned}$$
Therefore, there are exactly 11 integers $k$ such that $u(x)$ divides $33kfuthi$. So, the answer is $11$.;;;

