Response:  We are given that uMdladlo wokuphonsa indandatho (the number of cows in the field) is equal to 150 and we want to find out how many cows there will be after 7 years have passed. To do this, we need to multiply the current number of cows by a growth factor of 2. So, if we assume that each cow gives birth to one calf per year, then the total number of cows after 7 years will be:

umDladlo wokuphonsa indandatho x 2 = 150 x 2 = 300

